    "summary": "Topics: Gaming industry market trends (2024–2025), shift from original big-budget titles to IP-driven releases, risk mitigation in game publishing, user acquisition costs, long-term game operations, commercial model optimization, gameplay micro-innovation.\nEntities: 2024 original titles: 《绝区零》, 《鸣潮》, 《恋与深空》. 2025 original titles: 《奔奔王国》, 《可狱不可囚》, 《吸血鬼》. Key concepts: IP (Intellectual Property), mature commercial models, proven gameplay frameworks, user acquisition cost, long-operated products.\nDates: 2024, 2025.\nCore Claims: Major original big-budget games are nearly absent in 2025 compared to 2024. IP and proven gameplay models with micro-innovations are the core assets for hedging market uncertainty and securing baseline returns. 2025's successful original titles achieve success by reusing proven frameworks, optimizing mature commercial models, and executing efficient marketing, rather than through gameplay paradigm shifts. High user acquisition costs and entrenched player attention from long-operated games make IP adaptations/reboots safer and more efficient than original world-building. New games are expected to safely capture existing IP fan sentiment or meet validated user needs rather than create new worlds from scratch.\nEvidence Types: Comparative analysis of 2024 vs. 2025 new game rankings/lists; qualitative market condition observations. No tables, figures, quantitative metrics, formal definitions, or step-by-step procedures are present in this section.\nAnswerable Questions: What is the 2025 market trend for major original game releases? Why are publishers prioritizing IP and proven models in 2025? Which specific games exemplify the 2024 vs. 2025 new release shift? How do high user acquisition costs and long-operated games impact new product development strat..."
